We've configured mostly everything,
now in your project files add the following settings to your `nuxt.config.js` file.

In the 'head' section of the `nuxt.config.js` file add the follwing scripts:
script: [
  { src: 'https://cdn.polyfill.io/v2/polyfill.min.js?features=Element.prototype.classList' },
  { src: 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/focus-visible@5.0.2/dist/focus-visible.min.js' }
],

Then you can add the follwing css path and module settings for perfect Prismic & Nuxt harmony:
css: ['@/sliceMachine/styles/styles.scss'],

modules: [
  ['@nuxtjs/prismic', {
    endpoint: `https://{{ prismicDomain }}.cdn.prismic.io/api/v2`,
    linkResolver(doc) {
      if (doc.uid === 'page') {
        return doc.uid === 'homepage' ? '/' : `/${doc.uid}`
      }
      return '/'
    },
    routes: [
      '/:uid',
      '/',
    ]
  }]
],

After you've done this, launch your project by running:
`cd {{ projectName }} && npm run dev`
